
Overview of noun creole

The noun creole has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                       
1. Creole -- (a person of European descent born in the West Indies or Latin America)
2. Creole -- (a person descended from French ancestors in southern United States (especially Louisiana))
3. creole -- (a mother tongue that originates from contact between two languages)

Overview of adj creole

The adj creole has 2 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                        
1. Creole -- (of or relating to a language that arises from contact between two other languages and has features of both; "Creole grammars")
2. Creole -- (of or relating to or characteristic of native-born persons of French descent in Louisiana; "Creole cooking")
